On a big array, the method "System.Linq.Enumerable.Average(this IEnumerable<long> source)" (in .Net Core 2.1) throw the exception "OverflowException: Arithmetic operation resulted in an overflow.".
Why not use an algorithm that can prevent this, like :
```
double Average(this IEnumerable<long> source) {
double avg = 0;
int t = 1;
foreach (long x in source) {
avg += (((double)x) - avg) / ((double)t);
t += 1;
}
return avg;
}
```​

